This paper deals with scientometrics and collaboration among researchers, which is a topic that is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as it deals with collaboration and networks among researchers. The second likely sub-category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries), as it deals with the analysis of large datasets from the Web of Science database. The third likely sub-category is cs.CY (Computers and Society), as it deals with the social and ethical implications of collaboration and credit allocation in scientific research. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as it deals with the evaluation of the scientific impact of publications. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as it deals with the fairness and accountability of credit allocation in collaborative research.
